Crystal O'Connor , owner of Memories Pizza in Walkerton, Indiana , says she stands by her decision to never cater a gay wedding . 
  She has closed her store but said she will reopen and $850,000 has been raised in support of the business . 
  Comes after Indiana passed a new law that allows businesses to refuse to serve gays and lesbians . 
  On Saturday she said she does not hate gay people - she just does not support gay marriage . 
  Also on Saturday openly gay basketball star Jason Collins attended the Final Four in Indianapolis . 
 